# MEMORY.md and [LEARN]

- **On starting work:** If `MEMORY.md` exists, read it and follow any `[LEARN:...]` entries (citation fixes, notation, style). Do not repeat those mistakes.
- **When the user corrects you:** Append one line to `MEMORY.md`: `[LEARN:category] wrong → right` (e.g. `[LEARN:citation] Belloni (2014) → Belloni (2013)`). Use a short category; do not duplicate existing lines.

This keeps a persistent "error log" so future sessions stay consistent with past corrections.
